OL,3,GOPINIONCThe final weeks of the remnants
OL,4,Cof Grampian TV
OL,5,
OL,6,FThis covered the vast bulk of the
OL,7,Fpopulation but a relatively small
OL,8,Fproportion of the landmass.
OL,10,FInterestingly in 1960 the ITA proposed
OL,11,Fbuilding a transmitter between Perth
OL,12,Fand Dundee to improve reception there.
OL,13,FPresumably this would have been a relay
OL,14,Fof Blackhill. It was never built.
OL,16,FHowever by then the ITA had decided to
OL,17,Fgive a separate company, Grampian, the
OL,18,Ffranchise to broadcast on transmitters
OL,19,Fbeing built for Aberdeenshire and the
OL,20,Farea around Inverness.
